06:37.839 --> 06:43.344
♪ I want you to move
to California for yourself ♪

06:52.850 --> 06:54.951
STEVE: <i>We went out in search
of a way to say good-bye</i>

06:54.985 --> 06:56.653
<i>to an absent father,</i>

06:56.687 --> 06:58.154
<i>but we found</i>
<i>a lot more than that.</i>

06:58.189 --> 07:00.523
<i>We found each other.</i>

07:02.059 --> 07:04.027
<i>Not to mention ourselves.</i>

07:04.061 --> 07:06.663
<i>And like the open road...</i>

07:06.697 --> 07:09.532
<i>we are infinite.</i>

07:09.567 --> 07:12.402
Will you shut up?

07:12.436 --> 07:14.871
You've been narrating
for four hours.

07:18.442 --> 07:21.110
I can't believe
your dad is dead.

07:22.680 --> 07:24.614
Hey, how you doing?

07:24.648 --> 07:25.949
Fine.

07:25.983 --> 07:28.284
My dad was never there
for me when he was alive,

07:28.319 --> 07:29.999
so it doesn't feel
like anything's changed.

07:30.020 --> 07:32.922
I mean, he was in and out
of my life until I was eight,

07:32.957 --> 07:35.191
and then he disappeared
completely.

07:36.894 --> 07:39.362
I used to get all excited
when he was around

07:39.396 --> 07:41.531
'cause he'd give me Cheetos
for breakfast.

07:41.565 --> 07:44.167
It wasn't until I got older
that I came to understand

07:44.201 --> 07:47.270
that he did that because
he didn't care about me at a.

07:47.304 --> 07:49.739
He didn't even care enough
to get me real Cheetos.

07:49.773 --> 07:53.476
It was some off-brand knockoff
called "Cheese O's."

07:53.510 --> 07:56.145
I had no idea
that while I was swimming

07:56.180 --> 07:58.314
in name-brand snack foods,

07:58.349 --> 08:01.184
everything was so weird for you.

08:01.218 --> 08:02.919
I'm gonna need a minute, guys.

08:02.953 --> 08:04.954
(crying)

08:06.857 --> 08:10.159
SNOT: <i>Look, there's a
lonely hitchhiker.</i>

08:10.194 --> 08:13.429
Let's pick him up
and you can analyze him.

08:20.938 --> 08:22.372
Whew, thanks for the ride.

08:22.406 --> 08:24.741
I was standing out there
for quite a while.

08:24.775 --> 08:26.075
It's cool, man.

08:26.110 --> 08:28.244
We're on a pretty
heavy trip ourselves.

08:28.279 --> 08:29.946
His dad died.

08:29.980 --> 08:31.614
So, yeah, there's that.

08:31.649 --> 08:34.116
Oh, I'm sorry
to hear about that.

08:34.150 --> 08:35.585
Thanks, but I didn't really...

08:35.619 --> 08:37.220
Yeah.

08:37.254 --> 08:40.289
It's been pretty rough
on all of us.

08:40.323 --> 08:42.025
Barry, pull over.

08:42.058 --> 08:45.261
We need to wander
around the woods.

08:46.764 --> 08:48.531
You've been running
from your feelings, Snot.

08:48.565 --> 08:50.633
But that ends here.

08:50.668 --> 08:52.902
The only thing
more natural than nature

08:52.937 --> 08:54.804
is feelings.

08:54.838 --> 08:56.639
Okay, I'm out.

08:56.674 --> 08:58.541
I don't think I can
relate to this journey.

08:58.575 --> 09:00.643
The truth is I have a
serious meth addiction

09:00.678 --> 09:02.912
and I need to get to an
underpass before nightfall.

09:02.947 --> 09:05.081
Good luck and Godspeed.

09:07.518 --> 09:09.519
(birds chirping)

09:26.036 --> 09:28.604
That could be
your dad right now.

09:28.639 --> 09:30.873
Ca-caw!

09:30.908 --> 09:32.909
♪

10:00.304 --> 10:03.039
♪

10:32.102 --> 10:34.103
♪

10:42.546 --> 10:44.547
What the hell is that thing?

10:44.581 --> 10:46.249
It represents your dad.

10:46.283 --> 10:49.752
I was thinking you could scream
at it or burn it or something.

10:49.787 --> 10:51.054
I'm not gonna do that.

10:51.088 --> 10:53.056
Snot, you need to process this!

10:53.090 --> 10:54.590
This is a big deal!

10:54.625 --> 10:56.159
Yeah, it's my big deal!

10:56.193 --> 10:58.027
And I am not gonna
pretend to have

10:58.062 --> 11:00.596
some big theatrical
reaction to this

11:00.631 --> 11:02.899
just to make you happy!

11:02.933 --> 11:04.934
But you should have
<i>some</i> reaction.

11:04.968 --> 11:06.335
You have to feel something!

11:06.370 --> 11:07.804
He was your dad.

11:07.838 --> 11:09.338
And now he's gone.

11:10.374 --> 11:12.408
We're all gonna die, Steven!

11:12.443 --> 11:14.010
I'm gonna die!

11:14.044 --> 11:15.378
You're gonna die!

11:15.412 --> 11:17.914
Everyone dies!
(thunder crashes)

11:17.948 --> 11:20.349
Do you really think any of this

11:20.384 --> 11:22.552
is going to last forever?

11:22.586 --> 11:24.153
'Cause it's not!

11:24.188 --> 11:26.556
Your dad's death
is tearing us apart!

11:28.225 --> 11:30.193
(grunting)

11:30.227 --> 11:32.829
(sobbing)

11:32.863 --> 11:36.399
We are all alone
in the universe.

11:36.433 --> 11:37.633
We are not alone!

11:37.668 --> 11:39.202
We're in this together!

11:39.236 --> 11:43.239
We are born alone
and we die alone.

11:43.273 --> 11:45.374
Why am I here?

11:45.409 --> 11:46.375
(thunder crashes)

11:46.410 --> 11:48.578
I don't know why I'm here.

11:48.612 --> 11:50.513
Wait a minute.
Where's Toshi?

11:50.547 --> 11:51.948
Toshi?

11:51.982 --> 11:54.117
Tosh!

11:57.521 --> 11:59.021
BARRY:
Toshi!

11:59.056 --> 12:00.923
Toshi, where are you?

12:00.958 --> 12:02.825
Toshi, please come back!

12:02.860 --> 12:05.528
Toshi!

12:11.735 --> 12:13.736
(panting)

12:15.506 --> 12:18.541
It's so hot in this corn.

12:18.575 --> 12:20.476
STEVE:
I found him!

12:28.585 --> 12:30.219
What are you talking about?

12:35.192 --> 12:37.059
Please go.

12:51.842 --> 12:54.076
The secret to
the "Piece of Cake" system

12:54.111 --> 12:56.112
is the real aluminum wire,

12:56.146 --> 12:58.147
which is spun to perfection
in China.

12:58.182 --> 13:00.249
Where they know
how to spin wire.

13:00.284 --> 13:01.918
This wire is safe to touch.

13:01.952 --> 13:03.920
You will not cut yourself
on this wire.

13:03.954 --> 13:05.988
This wire retracts into
the handles for easy storage.

13:06.023 --> 13:08.057
I could just go on and on
about this wire,

13:08.091 --> 13:09.392
but the real proof
is in the puddin',

13:09.426 --> 13:11.027
or the cake,
as I should have said,

13:11.061 --> 13:12.695
because we are about
to slice up some cake!

13:12.729 --> 13:13.763
I don't know about you,

13:13.797 --> 13:16.832
but I am glad I came
to work today.

13:16.867 --> 13:18.534
Now, just watch this.
Look at this.

13:18.569 --> 13:20.036
Watch and see how
amazing this is.

13:20.070 --> 13:21.437
Look! Look! Look! Look!

13:21.471 --> 13:22.872
Look at this!
Look at this! Look!

13:22.906 --> 13:25.641
Now, I've heard stories
of people running this system

13:25.676 --> 13:29.278
under hot water
and using it on ice-cream cake!

13:32.950 --> 13:35.084
We don't have time to
dillydally, so we're just

13:35.118 --> 13:36.552
going to get a room, shower up,

13:36.587 --> 13:38.788
and then get right back
on the road.

13:51.201 --> 13:52.602
Um, hi.

13:52.636 --> 13:54.837
Uh, can I help you
with your cello?

13:54.871 --> 13:56.806
No. It's my suitcase.

13:56.840 --> 13:58.541
I just don't think
all suitcases

13:58.575 --> 14:00.076
should be rectangles, you know?

14:00.110 --> 14:01.477
I think sometimes suitcases

14:01.511 --> 14:03.646
can be cello cases
with clothes in them.

14:04.982 --> 14:06.482
What are you doing here?

14:06.516 --> 14:08.784
I'm traveling cross-country
taking Polaroid pictures

14:08.819 --> 14:11.053
of people walking
other people's dogs.

14:11.088 --> 14:12.455
It's pretty hard to tell,

14:12.489 --> 14:13.889
but I didn't become an artist

14:13.924 --> 14:15.558
because it was easy.

14:15.592 --> 14:16.926
You're amazing.

14:16.960 --> 14:19.562
I'm actually a total dork.

14:19.596 --> 14:21.464
I got to get something to eat.

14:21.498 --> 14:23.299
I'm starving.

14:24.868 --> 14:27.503
(fluorescent lights humming)

14:34.144 --> 14:36.145
(coins clatter
into vending machine)

15:03.507 --> 15:08.678
Where were you?!
Where were you?!

15:08.712 --> 15:10.279
Where were you?!

15:10.314 --> 15:12.214
(sobbing)

15:28.065 --> 15:29.465
WOMAN:
Move.

15:29.499 --> 15:33.169
You can move that way
or you can move that way,

15:33.203 --> 15:35.204
but you got to move.

15:39.343 --> 15:41.544
You're right.

15:41.578 --> 15:43.913
I've been frozen inside.

15:43.947 --> 15:45.314
Stuck.

15:45.349 --> 15:46.349
Now I understand

15:46.383 --> 15:48.317
what Steve was trying
to do for me.

15:48.352 --> 15:50.519
I got to get to this funeral.

15:50.554 --> 15:52.521
I've got to move.

15:52.556 --> 15:53.889
Yes, move.

15:53.924 --> 15:55.358
I must clean.

15:55.392 --> 15:57.927
Frat boys poop all over room.

15:57.961 --> 16:00.129
And in the lobby!

16:00.163 --> 16:03.833
They only do this
'cause I Tri Delt.

16:08.023 --> 16:10.191
Yeah, so his dad is dead

16:10.225 --> 16:11.793
and we're heading
to the funeral.

16:11.827 --> 16:13.261
It's rough, because his dad

16:13.295 --> 16:15.196
was never really
there for him, so...

16:15.230 --> 16:17.432
you know,
it's-it's rough.

16:17.466 --> 16:19.534
He's also pretty poor.

16:19.568 --> 16:21.135
Well, with a friend like you,

16:21.170 --> 16:23.538
he's got more than most.

16:26.575 --> 16:28.376
(whispering): I'm gonna
leave this picture

16:28.410 --> 16:29.877
at a gas station.

16:34.683 --> 16:35.917
Steve, I get it now.

16:35.951 --> 16:38.086
I get why I have to go
to my dad's funeral.

16:38.120 --> 16:39.587
And I owe it all to you.

16:39.621 --> 16:40.688
That-that's great, buddy.

16:40.723 --> 16:42.390
And I want to talk all about it

16:42.424 --> 16:43.524
the minute you get back.

16:43.559 --> 16:45.560
Just you and me
in the buddy closet.

16:45.594 --> 16:48.930
You're not going with me
to my dad's funeral?

16:48.964 --> 16:51.499
I would love to,
but-but this girl,

16:51.533 --> 16:54.268
this-this incredibly
hard-to-define girl...

16:56.605 --> 16:58.005
I think she's the one.

16:58.040 --> 16:59.540
And that I would meet her now,

16:59.575 --> 17:01.376
while you're going
through your thing...

17:01.410 --> 17:03.010
what wonderfully
transformative time

17:03.045 --> 17:04.212
for both of us!

17:04.246 --> 17:05.279
But...

17:05.314 --> 17:06.781
(grunts) Life.

17:06.815 --> 17:08.383
Am I right?

17:13.388 --> 17:15.455
I can't believe Steve bailed

17:15.491 --> 17:17.258
after everything
we've been through.

17:17.291 --> 17:19.694
Thanks for being here
for me, Barry.

17:19.728 --> 17:21.396
Hey, I just feel good

17:21.430 --> 17:23.431
taking you to your
dad's funeral.

17:37.012 --> 17:39.013
♪

17:42.851 --> 17:45.987
I just realized
I don't know your name.

17:46.021 --> 17:47.221
I could tell you my name,

17:47.256 --> 17:48.556
but would my name tell you

17:48.590 --> 17:50.992
that I'm incapable
of seeing the color orange?

17:51.026 --> 17:53.828
I just have to trust people
who give me these.

17:53.862 --> 17:57.131
Or that I think mustaches
are T-shirts for lips?

17:57.166 --> 17:59.801
Or that I wear
ice skates to weddings?

17:59.835 --> 18:01.569
It's hard to dance.

18:01.603 --> 18:04.071
But that's just the
type of person I am.

18:06.542 --> 18:07.842
I'm Steve.

18:07.876 --> 18:09.544
I'm the kind of guy
who drives cross-country

18:09.578 --> 18:11.612
to take his friend
to his old man's funeral,

18:11.647 --> 18:13.448
then gives it all up
when he finds

18:13.482 --> 18:16.217
his manic, pixie dream girl
along the way.

18:16.251 --> 18:17.552
Wait a minute.

18:17.586 --> 18:19.153
You blew off your
grieving friend

18:19.188 --> 18:22.023
to hang out in a hot tub
with a complete stranger?

18:22.057 --> 18:23.024
No.

18:23.058 --> 18:24.625
No, you don't understand.

18:24.660 --> 18:26.761
I helped him get in touch
with his sadness.

18:26.795 --> 18:29.730
I'm the only reason
he even went to the funeral.

18:29.765 --> 18:31.799
Oh, I just figured you out.

18:31.834 --> 18:33.835
You're an emotional tourist.

18:36.705 --> 18:37.672
A what?

18:37.706 --> 18:38.940
You're the kind of person

18:38.974 --> 18:40.741
who feeds off
other's experiences

18:40.776 --> 18:43.277
to fill the void inside of you.

18:43.312 --> 18:44.512
An emotional tourist.

18:44.546 --> 18:45.813
And I'm sorry,

18:45.848 --> 18:47.748
but that's not the
trip I packed for.

18:51.520 --> 18:53.721
(panting)

19:10.038 --> 19:12.473
STEVE:
<i>We're all searching.</i>

19:12.508 --> 19:14.008
<i>For something.</i>

19:14.042 --> 19:16.043
<i>Something that makes us</i>
<i>feel alive.</i>

19:21.049 --> 19:23.050
<i>Something to connect us.</i>

19:29.625 --> 19:31.592
♪

19:31.627 --> 19:33.628
<i>To give our lives meaning.</i>

19:37.766 --> 19:40.167
<i>But sometimes when you're</i>
<i>searching for something,</i>

19:40.202 --> 19:42.703
<i>the worst thing</i>
<i>that can happen is...</i>

19:42.738 --> 19:44.672
<i>you find it.</i>

19:48.110 --> 19:49.110
Well, we made it.

19:52.314 --> 19:54.148
(sniffs)

19:59.721 --> 20:02.189
So, now what?

20:02.224 --> 20:04.425
Just drive.

20:04.459 --> 20:07.228
A railroad gypsy took
away my vas deferens,

20:07.262 --> 20:09.230
but you are bumming me out.

20:09.264 --> 20:11.365
(sniffs)

20:26.782 --> 20:28.916
STEVE: <i>I should have
gotten out of the truck</i>

20:28.951 --> 20:30.585
<i>and given Snot a hug...</i>

20:30.619 --> 20:32.219
<i>but I couldn't face him.</i>

20:32.254 --> 20:34.755
<i>I chose a girl</i>
<i>over my best friend.</i>

20:34.790 --> 20:37.658
<i>And it'll haunt me</i>
<i>the rest of my life.</i>

20:39.695 --> 20:42.897
TRUCK DRIVER: <i>I've seen a lot of
strange things in my long life,</i>

20:42.931 --> 20:44.398
<i>in between the blinks,</i>

20:44.433 --> 20:46.763
<i>but that was definitely</i>
<i>the weirdest kid</i>

20:46.883 --> 20:48.901
<i>I ever drove away</i>
<i>from a funeral.</i>

20:49.508 --> 20:51.440
<i>And I'm usually up</i>
<i>for anything.</i>

